Script,Minor_Suit_Slam
window.currentPBSScenario = 'Minor_Suit_Slam';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Minor_Suit_Slam';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for Minor_Suit_Slam');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'Minor_Suit_Slam',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: 21GF-DEFAULT
convention-card-ew: 21GF-GIB
*/
# curate: kind=bidding
# convention-card-ns: 21GF-DEFAULT
# convention-card-ew: 21GF-GIB


# North opens 1NT; South (student, responder) holds a long strong minor with
# slam values and drives to a minor-suit slam.
dealer north

##### Imported Script -- GIB 1 Notrump (North) #####

# GIB opens 1N w/15-17 HCP or 15-16 and a 5-card major
ntP = hcp(north) + shape(north,5xxx+x5xx)
nt1 = shape(north, any 5332+any 4432+any 4333) and hcp(north)>14 and ntP<18

# GIB does not open with 5422 and a 5-card major or with 4 spades
# GIB does not open with 5422 and the strength to reverse
nt2 = shape(north, any 5422-5xxx-x5xx-4xxx) and hcp(north)>14 and hcp(north)<17

gibNT = nt1 or nt2

### End of GIB 1 Notrump (North) ###
# Defines gibNT  (North opens a 15-17 1NT)
##### Imported Script: Define Calm Opponents #####

# Avoid concentration of values
cce = top4(east,clubs)<2
cde = top4(east,diamonds)<2
che = top4(east,hearts)<2
cse = top4(east,spades)<2
noConEast = cce and cde and che and cse

ccw = top4(west,clubs)<2
cdw = top4(west,diamonds)<2
chw = top4(west,hearts)<2
csw = top4(west,spades)<2
noConWest = ccw and cdw and chw and csw

balEast    = shape(east,any 4432 +any 4333)
unbalEast  = shape(east,xxxx -any 4432 -any 4333 -any 9xxx -any 8xxx -any 7xxx-any 6xxx -any 55xx)

balWest    = shape(west,any 4432 +any 4333)
unbalWest  = shape(west,xxxx -any 4432 -any 4333 -any 9xxx -any 8xxx -any 7xxx-any 6xxx -any 55xx)

calmEast = (unbalEast and noConEast and hcp(east)<8) or (balEast and hcp(east)<11)
calmWest = (unbalWest and noConWest and hcp(west)<8) or (balWest and hcp(west)<11)
calmOpps = calmEast and calmWest

##### End of Imported Script: Define Calm Opponents #####
# Defines calmOpps

# South: a genuine source of tricks in one minor (6+ cards, 3+ of the top four
# honours), slam-going values, and no 4-card major to sidetrack into Stayman.
sLongClubs = clubs(south)>5    and top4(south,clubs)>2
sLongDiam  = diamonds(south)>5 and top4(south,diamonds)>2
sSource    = sLongClubs or sLongDiam
sNoMajor   = spades(south)<4 and hearts(south)<4
sSlam      = hcp(south)>14 and hcp(south)<19

gibNT and sSource and sNoMajor and sSlam and calmOpps

produce 1000
action printoneline,
`, "N", true)
Script
Button,Minor-Suit Slam,\n\
--- Minor-Suit Slam over 1NT\n\
Partner opens 1NT and you hold a long，strong minor -- a source of tricks --\n\
with slam values. Rather than ace-ask，transfer to (or show) your minor and use\n\
keycard once the fit is set，landing in six of the minor or 6NT.\n\
4NT is Roman Keycard Blackwood (1430) once a suit is agreed. Keycard responses:\n\
  • 5!C = 1 or 4 keycards\n\
  • 5!D = 0 or 3\n\
  • 5!H = 2 without the trump queen\n\
  • 5!S = 2 with the trump queen\n\
%Minor_Suit_Slam%
